 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-036 FINDING 3: TASK INFLATION. 328 open tasks, 136 'likely implemented' but not closed. 46 open EPICs (only 3 closed). The task system has become a burden rather than a tool. ROOT CAUSES: (1) Tasks are created speculatively during crystallization/observation — every observe/harvest creates candidate tasks. (2) EPICs are created for conceptual clusters but never systematically closed when their constituent tasks complete. (3) The audit function identifies likely-done tasks but doesn't auto-close them. (4) Many EPICs describe Phase E work (daemon, active observer, MCP extraction) that won't be needed for months. IMPACT: R(t) acquisition function is diluted across 328 candidates. The routing impact score spreads thin — top recommendation has impact=0.27 where ideal would be >0.5 for clear prioritization. Every session spends cognitive budget reading task lists instead of doing work. VERIFICATION: After closing 136 likely-done tasks + triaging EPICs to <80 open / <10 EPICs, R(t) top recommendation impact should increase to >0.40. SOLUTION: Batch close, EPIC triage, institute task decay (untouched 5+ sessions → P4)."
